{
  "stem": "1415.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And like I say, the bombing went on all the time after that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember being-- we specially went up, the three of us-- my friends from our hometown.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They are in the pictures too, from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they-- we-- we laid on the top.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we prayed for those bombs to come so badly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We wanted-- we knew that this was meant-- that we're going to be out of here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] about 10 days before liberation, I would say, maybe a day or two, or maybe it was before then that-- that the bombs fell and knocked out-- knocked out the electricity of the camp, so there was no more electric.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I think it might have been right after the last patrol.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, about 10 days before liberation, the German patrol [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] took away the last [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] people, because they were taken away.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My brother was gone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, this was-- all through January, the people were just marching out, and it was less and less people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the whole camp next to us, my brother's camp, was completely empty.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And in our camp, even, they were emptying out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But about 10 days before liberation, the last patrol, I remember they came on motorcycles, like with an attached little wagon type.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they pulled up in front of our block.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I don't remember whether they took some of our children or not.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They might have, because some of them were bigger than others.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They might have taken some.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But they didn't take me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They-- they left us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And-- and they went to the hospital, evidently, because I found it out after liberation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they took my mother.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
